1.title: Music, Motors and Art
1.plot: Michael Schreiber of California is a Bike builder and Art Gallery operator. Michael used to work for Harley Davidson but did what most of us only dream of doing. Michael sold his classic car to raise money for the new business venture and laid it all on the line. Michael quit his day job and went to build his dream. No he says his best days are ahead of him and he doesn't look back.

2.title: Lordz of Kustomz
2.plot: Jesse Castillo grew up on the streets of South LA and built the first lo-rider bicycle in the city. Soon Jesse would realise that his obsession with machines would take him much further than he ever dreamed. Today Jesse builds chops for international customers and at the same time runs a workshop that gives the street kids of the neighbourhood some meaning to life. This is Jesse's dream.

plot: '_Garage Dreams_ (qv)' captures the mosaic of modern auto culture through an engaging human story driven format. The narrative focuses on the people behind these beautiful machines and their heartfelt journeys through the build process. This collection of character-driven stories celebrates passion, authenticity and the human spirit.
synopsis: Garage Dreams captures the mosaic of modern auto culture in an engaging human story driven format. Its not so much the horsepower of interest here but more the people behind these beautiful machines. The inclusive stories celebrate passion, authenticity and human spirit and so appeal to a broader general entertainment audience than performance based car shows.Each episode comprises unique and compelling personal tales about a special car or bike project and provides a window into the sub-culture of these aficionados. The series examines in beautiful detail the gritty streets of South Central Los Angeles, the emerging bike building collectives in Asia and is anchored by the progressive scene around Melbourne, the auto culture capital of Australia.Style cues, inspirations, fashion, music and film are readily explored as we get deeper into these biographical accounts. Designed to reflect on the traditions of the hand-crafted workshop movement and also speak to the new-age collector set, this series is positioned to appeal to the selective auto culture audience that is rapidly defining a global mainstream lifestyle.
